    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-17T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-17T10:00:00-05:00" n="129"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d129">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A5/508: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bingham</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-17T15:00:00+00:00"
                            >October 17, 1935—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 17—9:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>522. By appointment Atherton and Anderson called at the Foreign Office today and
                    set forth the points of Department’s 300, October 14, 6 p.m., which the British
                    received with evident satisfaction. A précis of conversation was left, based on
                    the Department’s instruction (copies by pouch tomorrow<note n="80"
                        xml:id="d129fn80">Embassy’s despatch No. 1760, October 17, not
                        printed.</note>) and the British will seek another meeting shortly, after
                    they have studied it, and formulated a précis of conversation for reply.</p>
                <p>It was agreed that these précis of conversation would not constitute an “exchange
                    of written official papers or memoranda”.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bingham</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
